         <METS:xmlData>
            <dc:title xml:lang="slv">Fragmenti o mitu in zgodovini</dc:title>
            <dc:creator>Štepec, Marko</dc:creator>
            <dc:subject xml:lang="slv">zgodovinopisje</dc:subject>
            <dc:subject xml:lang="slv">mit</dc:subject>
            <dc:subject xml:lang="slv">antisemitizem</dc:subject>
            <dc:subject xml:lang="eng">Historiography</dc:subject>
            <dc:subject xml:lang="eng">myth</dc:subject>
            <dc:subject xml:lang="eng">anti-Semitism</dc:subject>
            <dc:publisher>Zveza Zgodovinskih društev Slovenije, Ljubljana</dc:publisher>
            <dc:contributor>Mitja Ferenc (ur.)</dc:contributor>
            <dc:contributor>Branka Petkovšek (ur.)</dc:contributor>
            <dc:contributor>Nives Sulič Dular (prev. ang.)</dc:contributor>
            <dc:contributor>Matjaž Klemenčič (prev. ang.)</dc:contributor>
            <dc:contributor>Stanislav Južnič (prev. ang.)</dc:contributor>
            <dc:date xsi:type="dcterms:W3CDTF">2006</dc:date>
            <dc:type xsi:type="dcterms:DCMIType">Text</dc:type>
            <dc:language xsi:type="dcterms:ISO639-3">slv</dc:language>
            <dcterms:alternative xml:lang="eng">Fragments on Myths and History</dcterms:alternative>
            <dcterms:abstract xml:lang="slv">Prispevek obravnava razmerja med mitskim in stereotipnim mišljenjem v nasprotju z zgodovinsko zavestjo. O mitskih predstavah spregovori kot o nujni posledici ideologizacije zgodovine in prepletenosti različnih »ideoloških mrež«. Posebno pozornost posveti povezovanju zgodovinopisja z oblikovanjem nacionalne zavesti in s tem povezanimi problemi marginalizacij na primeru slovenskega antisemitizma. V zavedanju lastne vpetosti v »ideološke mehanizme«, samorefleksiji zgodovinopisne misli in razširitvi preučevanja na celovit svet preteklih predstav, prepozna način kako preseči »mitsko«, stereotipno in ideološko v pogledih na preteklost.«</dcterms:abstract>
            <dcterms:abstract xml:lang="eng">Depicted is the relationship between myths and stereotype thinking as opposed to historical awareness. Mythic notions are a necessary result of historical ideologization and of interconnection of diverse »ideological networks.« Emphasized is the connection between historiography and the formation of national awareness, and the related problem of marginalization, illustrated by Slovene anti-Semitism. Only by becoming aware of its own shortcomings, of being entangled in »ideological mechanisms«, by thorough self-examination, and by extending the topic of its research on the entire world of past concepts will historiography be able to transcend the mythic, the stereotype, and ideologically colored views of the past.</dcterms:abstract>
            <dcterms:isPartOf>Zbirka Zgodovinskega časopisa ; 32</dcterms:isPartOf>
